{
  "source_note": "Keeper Rulebook Table XVII: Weapons (pp.401-405). Each row maps a canonical weapon to its skill, damage expression (excluding the attacker's damage bonus), base range in yards (null for melee/touch), uses per round, magazine capacity (null when not applicable), malfunction number (null when not applicable), whether it impales on an Extreme success, a special note, and the eras in which it is commonly available. Melee weapons add the attacker's damage bonus (adds_damage_bonus=true); firearms do not. Shotguns use range_banded_damage giving the close/half-range/max-range damage. Source: chapter 16 appendices, pp.401-405.",
  "schema": {
    "name": "weapon key, ASCII snake_case",
    "display_name": "canonical printable name",
